380 U.S. 519

85 S.Ct. 1325

Herbert E. CALLENDER et al.
v.
FLORIDA.

No. 58.

Supreme Court of the United States

April 26, 1965

Carl Rachlin and Floyd McKissick, for petitioners.

James W. Kynes, Atty. Gen. of Florida, and George R. Georgieff, Asst. Atty. Gen., for respondent.

On Petition for Writ of Certiorari to the Supreme Court of Florida.

PER CURIAM.

1

The petition for writ of certiorari is granted and the judgments are reversed. Boynton v. Com. of Virginia, 364 U.S. 454, 81 S.Ct. 182, 5 L.Ed.2d 206, Abernathy v. State of Alabama, 380 U.S. 447, 85 S.Ct. 1101.
